<br>
Logged into Emain the other night and ran through the doors of APK, before I had even finished typing /y 50 merc lfg, I received an invite which I accepted. Now the first thing I do is type Hi to the group then check out who or what I am grouping with, imagine my surprise as I saw the following.<br>
<br>
Sorc<br>
Merc<br>
Merc<br>
Merc<br>
Cleric<br>
Me = Merc<br>
Pally<br>
<br>
I knew it was going to be interesting, I just didn't realise how interesting.<br>
<br>
We worked out who was going to be MA and made our macros and headed off. For the next 3 hours we ran amok, chewing through Mid and Hib support toons, then tanks like there was no tomorrow. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is what I made my Merc for, to see enemies die under flashing blades, Hehe for 3 hours I was in Merc heaven. <br>
<br>
I don't expect it to ever happen again, as it was the quintessential pickup group, none of us had ever grouped together before and we just clicked right off, it was certainly an interesting experience.<br>
